Sorry guys but I am completely blocked from seeding.  OTOH, the other identical upload is seeding well.  Looks like the movie/music industry is winning because the American ISP providers have agreed to help them by throttling and closing accounts.  My advice is to get what you can when you can.  

AVOID a service called (HMA - Hide My Ass) who entice you in claiming they can hide your IP but the moment you start seeding they warn then shut you off claiming pressure from the Movie industry.

OTOH, GTGuard, which uses a proxy/Socks 5 connection and runs your data up/down through their servers has been solid.  Does require you to backlevel some P2P apps that support Socks 5 (Transmission v1.72 and VUSE are good).
